CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 13, 1953, pg. 16, reads: "PLENTY OF FREE SAMPLES in BOOTHS...some of the 3,000 persons who attended four sessions of the Home Service Fair are shown as they inspected the booths of the various merchants."
TitMainTitle: Men, and women, including one wearing eyeglasses and braids piled on head, drinking from cup, beside Best Foods, A & P Food Stores, Philip Morris, and House of Beauty Cosmetics booths, for 1953 Pittsburgh Courier Home Service Fair, Ammon Center
